    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n- No easy way to download a file, though both `curl` and libuv are available in all Nvim targets.\n- `:edit <uri>` (example: `:edit https://example.com/foo.txt`) is dependent on netrw for no reason\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nseparate PRs:\n\n* [ ] introduce something like `vim.fetch()` (`vim.net.fetch()` ? idk, look at Go, NodeJS, for precedent)\n    - could use `curl` or `vim.loop`\n* [ ] use it to implement `:edit <uri>` without netrw\n* [ ] use it to implement spellfile download. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/7189\n\n\n### Related\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23231\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/4378\n\n### Use-cases in the wild\n\n- https://github.com/3rd/image.nvim/blob/88e9693e188b8464b1c426aebb4389fd9db2fcbf/lua/image/image.lua#L393",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Is there a preference on how the underlying implementation should be?\r\n\r\n- shell out to `curl`\r\n- `libcurl` binding\r\n- `vim.loop` based\r\n- existing lua libraries (e.g. `luasocket`)\r\n\r\nAnd preference on how the interface should be?\r\n\r\n- `fetch` api (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org)\r\n- something else?",
